Reasoning: The paper discusses the vulnerabilities of crypto currencies to double spending attacks and the mechanisms that implement them, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also discusses the hash rate and protection against double spending attacks, which relates to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also presents a theory of programmed self-destruction of crypto currencies, which could be categorized under game theory (cs.GT) or information theory (cs.IT).
